---
import Layout from '~/layouts/NesthingLayout.astro';
import ResilienceCTA from '~/components/ResilienceCTA.astro';
---

<Layout metadata={{ title: 'Data Governance & Privacy Protocol | Nesthing' }}>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-black text-white antialiased">
    <header class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-12 border-b border-[var(--color-linear-border)]">
      <span class="text-xs font-mono text-amber-400 tracking-widest uppercase block mb-3">Security & Compliance</span>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">Privacy & Data Governance Protocol</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 font-mono mt-2">Last Updated: June 2026 | Deployment Version 4.2</p>
    </header>

    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 prose prose-invert max-w-none text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-10">
      
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white tracking-tight">1. Architectural Scope & Zero-Retention Policy</h2>
        <p>
          At AIO Shield, we engineer closed-loop systems. For all implementations involving our **Primary Engine (Alpha) built on n8n multi-node frameworks**, data transit is executed purely via transient memory. 
        </p>
        <p class="border-l-2 border-cyan-500 pl-4 text-gray-400 bg-[var(--color-linear-card)]/20 p-3 rounded-r-xl">
          <strong>Zero Data Retention:</strong> Client credentials, raw inquiries, and legal/medical intake payloads passing through our secure webhooks are instantly mapped to your designated internal CRM. AIO Shield infrastructure does not retain database weights or logs of your consumer data post-execution.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white tracking-tight">2. Telemetry & Generative Search Engineering</h2>
        <p>
          For services under our **Assisting Engine (Beta) specializing in Generative Engine Optimization (GEO)**, we process publicly indexable entity data. We do not inject or train public Large Language Models (LLMs) on your proprietary trade secrets or unencrypted corporate intellectual properties. All RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) node injections strictly comply with global AI compliance frameworks and safety firewalls.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white tracking-tight">3. Edge Communications & Routing Security</h2>
        <p>
          Inbound client communications directed toward our public secure gateway (<code class="text-cyan-400 font-mono">howtodo@nesthing.com</code>) are processed at the network edge utilizing secure Cloudflare Mail Routing protocols. This infrastructure obfuscates core back-end server locations, neutralizes credential harvesting scripts, and mitigates malicious vector attacks before data hits our systems.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white tracking-tight">4. Regional Compliance Standards</h2>
        <p>
          Our automation models are rigorously tailored to prevent compliance leaks, specifically adhering to the **Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA)** and international architectural data transfer rules. No third-party API nodes utilized in our custom workflows are granted persistent access to sensitive data pillars.
        </p>
      </section>
<ResilienceCTA lang="en" whatsappNumber="60128631019" />
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": "Privacy & Data Governance Protocol",
  "description": "The technical compliance, data retention boundaries, and security architecture governing AIO Shield workflows and automated pipelines.",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Nesthing"
  },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "DigitalDocument",
    "name": "Privacy Protocol",
    "governance": "PDPA Compliance, Zero-Data Retention Automation Frameworks"
  }
}
</script>